parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to sway or wobble violently, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents, serious injury, or death.
symptoms: The vehicle sways or wobbles violently
especially at high speeds
making it difficult to control; the rear end of the vehicle may fishtail or rock back and forth; the driver and passengers may experience neck snapping back and forth.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear strut and suspension can cause the vehicle to shake violently, lose control, and potentially roll over, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes violently
loses control
and rocks back and forth uncontrollably
especially at high speeds; the steering wheel feels loose; the vehicle's tires may scuff or wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the front suspension housing and struts can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and injuries.
